title: GTEC USV: Output Load per Phase
agents: snmp
catalog: hw/power/gtec
license: GPLv3
distribution: kuhn-ruess

description:
 This check monitors the output load percentage of each of the three
 phases of a GTEC uninterruptible power supply (USV/UPS). The values are
 read via SNMP from the GTEC enterprise MIB
 (.1.3.6.1.4.1.935.1.1.1.8.3.5-7).

 The check goes WARN or CRIT when the output load of a phase exceeds the
 configured upper levels. By default it warns at 85% and goes critical at
 90%.

 The levels can be configured with the rule "Levels for output load of an
 UPS" (ruleset {ups_out_load}).

item:
 The name of the phase, one of {"phase 1"}, {"phase 2"} or {"phase 3"}.

discovery:
 One service is created for each of the three phases reported by the
 device.
